A source with knowledge of the incident confirmed to TMG Digital that the soldier accompanied by his attorney arrived at the Inanda Police Station on Thursday night. The infantryman had been on the run for nearly 48 hours after a shooting spree on Tuesday.He is alleged to have stormed a family home while looking for his girlfriend whom he believed was cheating on him. Inside he gunned down her sister and wounded another relative.In a second shooting a while later - after he kidnapped his girlfriend's brother to make him help search for her - he wounded a police officer who confronted him. Another person was also injured brining the total to three injured and one dead.Military police had been stationed at his family home at Inanda on Thursday as a joint task force followed leads to find him.SANDF spokesperson Mafi Mgobozi could not be reached for comment.-TMG Digital/TimesLIVE